Title: Asymptotic freedom and Confinement imply spontaneously broken chiral

symmetry in Quantum ChromodynamicsAuthors: R. Acharya and P. Narayana Swamy

Comments: Latex, 7 pages

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A12 (1997) 1649-1654

We utilize Coleman's theorem and show that quantum chromodynamics based onasymptotic freedom and confinement must have chiral symmetry realized as aspontaneously broken symmetry.